Quarterly Brief

State of GoPlus Q2 2025

Natalie Drake
Whynonah

Sep 8, 2025 ⋅  9 min read

Key Insights

  • GoPlus experienced growth across several metrics during Q1, including token price (+11.0%), ecosystem profit (+65.3%), GPS Locker TVL v2 (+511.3%) and v3 (+8.8%), and average daily blockchain request volume across supported networks (+34.8%).
  • GoPlus saw declines in average daily API query volume (-8.3%).
  • The team launched GoPlus-MCP, an MPC server that provides LLMs direct access to its security infrastructure, allowing users to run security checks and threat analyses via queries.
  • Product updates included the release of GoPlus Chrome Extension v0.2.6 and SafeToken Locker v4, which added new DeFi features to the extension and expanded Locker support to Uniswap V4 pools.

Primer

GoPlus (GPS) is a decentralized, user-driven security network designed to protect Web3 users and developers from the growing threats of scams, phishing attacks, and malicious token contracts. The platform operates on two core layers: the Security Data Layer and the Security Compute Layer, which aggregate, verify, and process real-time security data across multiple blockchains and decentralized applications. This architecture enables the detection and prevention of onchain risks, providing security services such as token analysis, phishing detection, and transaction risk assessments.

GoPlus’s SecWare protocol serves as a marketplace for developers to create and deploy modular security services (e.g., anti-scam and anti-phishing tools) within decentralized applications. Meanwhile, users can customize their security experience through SecHubs, which are personal security centers accessible via the GoPlus application. Other key tools include SecScan, which automates malicious token detection, and Mufuzz, an AI-powered fuzz testing engine for uncovering vulnerabilities in smart contracts. Innovations like phishing site detection and address detection leverage advanced machine learning models to identify threats across onchain and offchain ecosystems.

Website / X (Twitter) / Discord

Key Metrics

Financial Analysis

Market Cap and Price

Relative to BTC and ETH, which saw their market caps increase by 30.3% and 36.6% QoQ, respectively, GoPlus’s market cap increased 0.1% QoQ from $46.1 million in Q1 2025 to $46.2 million in Q2 2025. GPS’s token price recorded a greater QoQ increase, rising 11.0% from $0.0254 to $0.0282.

Ecosystem Profit

Ecosystem profit reflects revenue generated through GoPlus services, primarily from active SecHubs; however, it is worth noting that GoPlus is actively shifting its focus toward scaling API and Chrome extension products rather than promoting new SecHub creation. In Q2 2025, GoPlus’s ecosystem profit totaled $154,949, up 65.3% QoQ from $93,733 in Q1. The average daily profit also increased 65.3% QoQ from $1,041 in Q1 to $1,722 in Q2.

Network Analysis

API Query Volume

Authorized API query volume tracks the number of calls made to GoPlus's security APIs, which support features like token checks, malicious address detection, and phishing alerts. This offchain metric includes blockchain-level interactions (e.g., transaction simulations and malicious address detection) within the network infrastructure.

In Q2 2025, authorized API query volume averaged 28.0 million per day, representing an 8.3% decrease from the Q1 daily average of 30.5 million.

Blockchain Request Volume

This offchain metric includes blockchain-level interactions (e.g., transaction simulations and malicious address detection) within the network infrastructure. In contrast, authorized API request volume specifically measures API calls made by external users and platforms interacting directly with GoPlus's services.

In Q2 2025, blockchain request volume increased across all major networks. The “Others” category (representing 41 chains) recorded the largest QoQ increase, with total requests rising 78.5%, going from 27.7 million in Q1 to 49.4 million in Q2. BNB Chain followed with a 74.0% QoQ increase from 227.4 million in Q1 to 395.7 million in Q2. The next largest increase was Avalanche with a 44.0% QoQ increase from 8.3 million in Q1 to 11.9 million in Q2.

The substantial growth in the “Others” category can be attributed to GoPlus’s expansion to 15 additional blockchains in Q2, increasing the category from 26 chains in Q1 to 41 chains in Q2.

GoPlus Chrome Extension

The GoPlus Chrome extension strengthens user security by detecting phishing sites, risky transactions, and wallet vulnerabilities. In Q2 2025, the total number of protected transactions decreased 22.9% QoQ, from 9.7 million to 7.4 million. The total number of Chrome Extension downloads also fell 98.4% QoQ from 215,714 to 3,444. The larger decrease in extension downloads compared to protected transactions suggests that GoPlus extension activity is being driven by consistent users.

Locker TVL

GoPlus Locker is a security tool that allows token projects to lock tokens and liquidity pool (LP) assets in a decentralized and transparent manner. The v2 Locker, which supports Uniswap V2 pools, represents the earlier version of GoPlus’s LP locking infrastructure and offers fundamental asset-locking capabilities. The v3 Locker, which supports Uniswap V3 pools, introduced multichain support, an improved user interface, and greater flexibility for structuring locks across networks. The v4 Locker was released in May 2025, further expanding support to Uniswap V4 pools.

At the end of Q2 2025, GoPlus Lockers v2 and v3 held a combined total value locked (TVL) of $33.1 million, ranking 3rd in terms of the overall market on DefiLlama. The combined TVL increased 9.0% QoQ from $30.3 million at the end of Q1. Per locker, the v2 locker recorded an 8.8% QoQ increase from $30.3 million to $33.3 million, and the v3 locker recorded a 511.3% QoQ increase from $7,812 to $47,759.

Qualitative Analysis

GoPlus-MCP

On May 20, 2025, GoPlus launched GoPlus-MCP, an MCP (model context protocol) server that allows LLMs direct access to GoPlus’s Web3 security tools and data. Users can use MCP supporting LLMs, such as Claude or DeepSeek, to query the security status of Web3 assets and receive real-time threat detection and security analysis. GoPlus-MCP security detection features include token security checks, phishing site detection, malicious address checks, NFT security checks, and token approval security analysis. These features are supported across 41 EVM and non-EVM compatible blockchains, covering notable chains such as Ethereum, BNB Chain, Polygon, Arbitrum, Solana, and Sui. To integrate GoPlus-MCP into an LLM, a user must install it globally via npm (Node Package Manager) and configure it with their GoPlus API credentials.

Buyback Program Completion

GoPlus completed its buyback program on April 15, 2025, burning ~177.2 million GPS (~$3.1 million USD at the time of burn). This initiative was part of a five-part recovery plan launched in response to community backlash over a sharp decline in GPS’s price following its Binance listing on March 4, 2025. The program used frozen market maker funds to buy back tokens, sending them to a designated burn address on Base. The buyback program was launched on March 23, 2025, with updates reported weekly.

  • March 26: The first buyback was completed, totaling ~34.9 million GPS bought back
  • March 31: The second buyback was completed, totaling ~89.0 million GPS bought back
  • April 7: The third buyback was completed, totaling ~105.2 million GPS bought back
  • April 13: The fourth buyback was completed, totaling ~136.7 million GPS bought back
  • April 14: The fifth buyback was completed, totaling ~175.6 million GPS bought back
  • April 15: ~177.2 million GPS were burned, marking the buyback program’s completion.

General Development and Growth

Despite mixed performance metrics, GoPlus broadened its security coverage across multiple ecosystems during Q2. The developments are listed below.

April:

  • Extended token security detection to Sonic, expanding security coverage to another Layer-1 ecosystem.
  • Integrated with Abstract to add token verification and enhance transaction security across the network.
  • Launched GPSignal, enabling token security checks through command posts on X (Twitter).
  • Expanded GoPlus Security Intelligence to Soneium, enabling token security detection across the new Layer-2.

May:

  • Integrated SafeToken Locker support on Manta Network, enhancing network trust and security with secure LP locking.
  • Extended GPSignal to SushiSwap, enabling users to run token security checks directly on SushiSwap.
  • Partnered with SpoonOS to integrate its API into SpoonOS’s AI agent ecosystem.
  • Updated the GoPlus Token Security API to detect hidden transaction taxes.
  • Partnered with UniDerp to integrate SafeToken Locker, delivering secure and transparent LP locking.
  • Integrated with Trust Wallet to provide in-wallet threat detection.
  • Released SafeToken Locker v4, adding support for Uniswap V4 pools.
  • Collaborated with Fibrous Finance to generate token risk readouts directly on the platform

June:

  • Integrated with Mira Network to embed GoPlus security screening into its AI chatbot.
  • Partnered with Web3 Decision to power its security audits, strengthening its smart audit engine with real-time verification and threat detection.
  • Upgraded the GoPlus Google Extension to v0.2.6, introducing a trading mode and a smart money monitoring feature.

Closing Summary

The broader crypto market saw substantial growth in Q2, with BTC and ETH market caps rising 30.3% and 36.6% QoQ, respectively. GoPlus experienced more modest market cap growth, rising 0.1% QoQ to $46.2 million, while the GPS token price increased 11.0% from $0.0254 to $0.0282.

Network metrics showed a mixed performance. Ecosystem profits increased, with total profits rising 65.3% QoQ to $154,949. Average daily request volume across supported networks recorded a 34.8% QoQ increase. Notably, request volume within the “Others” category of supported networks, representing 41 blockchains, surged 78.5% QoQ, driven by GoPlus’s expansion to 15 new blockchains. SafeToken Locker TVL for v2 and v3 also rose, recording a combined 9.0% QoQ increase from $30.3 million to $33.1 million. In contrast, average API query volume also decreased 8.3% QoQ to 28.0 million daily calls.

Other developments included the launch of GoPlus-MCP, an MCP server that allows LLMs direct access to GoPlus’s Web3 security tools, and an upgrade of the GoPlus Chrome extension to v0.2.6. The team also partnered with Trust Wallet and SushiSwap to integrate its security layer directly into their interfaces, and extended security to cover more networks such as Sonic and Abstract. These efforts reflect a continued commitment to expanding GoPlus and boosting overall Web3 security.
